name: Mung beans dahl
serves: 8
---
- 2tbsp olive oil
- 1 onion (chopped)
- 2 garlic clove
- 3tbsp ginger (2cm piece)
- 200g dry mung beans (or beluga lentils)
- 200g dry red lentils 
- 1tsp cumin
- 1tsp garam masala 
- 0.5tsp turmeric
- 0.5tsp salt
- 0.5tsp Sriracha sauce (hot pepper sauce. optional)
- 60g tomato paste
- 240g unsweetened coconut milk
- 350g brown rice
---
Preparation:
1.	Heat a medium pot with olive oil and fry the onion for 5 minutes until golden. 
2.	Add garlic and ginger and fry for a minute just until fragrant.
3.	Add the rest of the ingredients, pour water to 2 cm above covering and bring to a boil. Lower the flame, cover and cook for 40 minutes until the lentils are soft.
Serve over rice or quinoa.

